      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
         <p>The papers of Charles Goodwin Ridgely (1784-1848) span the years 1813-1826, with the bulk of the material concentrated between 1820 and 1822. The collection consists of a personal journal, a letterbook, and two letters. It relates chiefly to Ridgely's naval career, especially  his commands of the <emph render="italic">USS Erie</emph> (Sloop of war) during the War of 1812 and of the <emph render="italic">USS Constellation</emph> (Frigate) in the Pacific Squadron. Subjects include the Latin American policy of the United States Navy, the wars of independence in Chile and Peru, and Ridgely's attitude toward Spain and Latin American revolutionaries.
         </p>
      </scopecontent>
